docs.abstract: The former mayor of South Bend, Ind., has cherry-picked his record on minority poverty and arrests, overstated his consistency on health policy and used a questionable rationale to attack a rival.
docs.snippet: The former mayor of South Bend, Ind., has cherry-picked his record on minority poverty and arrests, overstated his consistency on health policy and used a questionable rationale to attack a rival.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg, the former mayor of South Bend, Ind., has had strong showings in the first two Democratic presidential nominating contests. As he seeks to build support ahead of Nevada’s vote on Saturday, Mr. Buttigieg has sought to explain his record with black residents of South Bend, distinguish himself from his competitors on health care, and parry attacks on the issue of campaign finance. Here’s a fact check.

headline.main: Fact-Checking Pete Buttigieg Before the Nevada Caucuses

docs.abstract: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos’s contentious regulations on sexual misconduct at schools will cement domestic and dating violence and stalking as forms of gender discrimination.
docs.snippet: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos’s contentious regulations on sexual misconduct at schools will cement domestic and dating violence and stalking as forms of gender discrimination.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos’s pending rules on sexual misconduct at the nation’s schools and colleges will include provisions to shore up protections for victims of stalking and dating violence, a response to lethal attacks that have underscored the weakness of current policies.

headline.main: New Campus Sexual Misconduct Rules Will Tackle Dating Violence
headline.print_headline: New Federal Rules Focus on Dating Violence on Campuses

docs.abstract: At a closed-door meeting, Speaker Nancy Pelosi urged Democrats to “keep our eye on the ball” and mocked President Trump’s skin color: “The ball has an orange face.”
docs.snippet: At a closed-door meeting, Speaker Nancy Pelosi urged Democrats to “keep our eye on the ball” and mocked President Trump’s skin color: “The ball has an orange face.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi, facing deep alarm among moderate Democrats who worry that Senator Bernie Sanders will win their party’s presidential nomination only to cost them control of the House, has begun distancing her caucus from the race for the White House in an effort to insulate her rank and file and preserve the party’s majority.

headline.main: Pelosi, Trying to Save House Majority, Fends Off Angst Over Sanders
headline.print_headline: Pelosi, Trying to Save House Majority, Seeks to Fend Off Angst Over Sanders

docs.abstract: The president ratcheted up a fight with a judicial system he sees as biased against him.
docs.snippet: The president ratcheted up a fight with a judicial system he sees as biased against him.
docs.lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — President Trump lashed out at two liberal Supreme Court justices on Tuesday, escalating his battle with the judicial system to new heights despite entreaties by his attorney general to refrain from attacks that complicate the administration’s legal fights.

headline.main: Trump, in India, Demands 2 Liberal Justices Recuse Themselves From His Cases
headline.print_headline: Trump Assails Supreme Court in a Startling Turn

docs.abstract: Nearly two months after the death of Iran’s most important general, the Trump administration insists its “maximum pressure” campaign is working. Many allies are skeptical.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States and Iran may have pulled back from the brink of war, but they have refused to stand down since the American drone strike in January that killed Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani, commander of Tehran’s elite Quds Force.

headline.main: U.S. Maintains Pressure on Iran, Stalling Diplomacy While Expecting Attacks
